If you’re anything like me then you enjoy a good old fashioned dynastic mystery series – the intrigue, the glamour, the betrayals, and the family tensions... Well, today I invite you to discover a fragrance family quite unlike any other and where nothing is quite as it seems... Penhaligon’s Portraits is a wittily named and beautifully presented collection of enticingly glamorous scents.  A tribute to those good old English eccentric, spirited characters that we recognise so well: stiff upper lip, caustic humour, and a knack for provocation... But which fragrance would you choose..?
@penhaligons_london

node.text:
It is a truth I must confess that when I’m hanging out a dress
I like the smell to be delightful, 
Always natural - nothing frightful

No nonsense, practical and plain, 
My focus must stay with the stain
Of course, I like it to look chic, 
The shelf appeal cannot be weak.

But what of cashmere, wool and mohair
And the things that take the most care?
No need to chemically dry clean -
Just wash by hand or home machine.

The stain solution will come first applying straight upon the spot
Say no to smells with scented vinegar - a soak will help a lot

Reversing items stops the fading, 
Then we bathe within a sink…
Ensuring temperatures are cool and all your colours are in synch.

Rinse through and press out excess water - never wring and never pull,
Allow to dry upon a towel, laying flat protects our wool, 

To speed the process roll up gently 
In same towel if needs be,
Safe in the knowledge that your woolens are phosphate and cruelty free 

Then we steam out any wrinkles 
And store folded good as new.
Take The ‘Dry’ out of your cleaning, From @TheLaundress, just for you. 💕

“Animals are such agreeable friends. They ask no questions, they pass no criticisms” George Elliot 

I was never the model of course, but my old working life was in fashion, and I always think that this title sentence sums up the turn my life has taken over the past decade!  My daily walks with Coco have lifted me out of many low moments this year, come rain or shine, and although I still love to dress up, you’re now more likely to find me with wellies paired with the frocks... Anyway - my husband, (having finally admitted defeat and acknowledged that I’m actually in love with my dog 😂) asked me to send him a few clips of film that I’d taken on various walks and then he recorded me answering a few questions.  Today he sent me this video as an ode to my love for Coco and I felt that it was too sweet not to share. I hope that you like it too. xx

#dog #dogsofinstagram #countrylife

The ‘OFFICIAL COVER REVEAL’!! 😆🎉🎉🎉
It’s the image that most people now associate with me and Hill House, so of course a version of it had to make it on to the cover of my book! To me the image signifies joy and happiness and finding a little pocket of peace in an otherwise ‘noisy’ world - and that’s what the book is all about!
Thanks to both @ninafuga for the illustration and @jimmylazergram for Art Direction, and of course the lovely @simonbrownphotography for capturing Hill House beautifully for the book. 

‘Hill House Living - The Art of Creating A Joyful Life’ is available to Pre-order now using the link in my bio, and will be out on October 14th in the UK published by @eburybooks and October 19th in the US published by @clarksonpotter . Happy Friday! 📚💕💕💕⭐️

About last night…
The past eighteen months seemed to have curbed my spontaneity, so when my husband suggested a late night picnic at Holkham beach yesterday, my initial instinct was to claim that it was far too late to organise…. However,  instead, I put my big girl pants on and faced up to the challenge of doing something completely unscheduled and away from my garden!! 😅 After all - all you really need for a ‘no-reason’ evening picnic is a glass of champagne and a cherry bakewell! 😂👍❤️
Have a wonderful Tuesday! xx (Notice that I’m posting at random times now too - WooHoo - watch out world!! 😳😂)

Hello sunshine!! Apparently it was supposed to be raining in Norfolk  today, so after a week of feeling ‘blah’ - I’m making the proverbial ‘hay whilst the sun shineth!’ 😆 Also, I didn’t plant a yellow Dahlia  and have no idea how this colour turned up in the mix…? However, it’s the first one out, it’s looking splendidly happy, and so I don’t mind a jot! Speaking of proverbs - perhaps the message here would be ‘A yellow Dahlia in the hand is worth two Cafe au Lait in the Bush?’ 😉 
Happy Monday! 🌞🌼💛xx

node.text:
There was a time when the only thing I knew how to grow was to grow tired and weary! I left London for the ‘Good Life’ but immediately found a field full of self doubt and a garden full of self discovery way before I eventually found my feet. Let’s call it going through a bit of “Good Grief!” before you reach the Good Life! Whatever you may imagine you see in my smiling images, it certainly wasn’t an overnight success story filled with unicorns, roses and me singing to imaginary bluebirds to find my route to contentment…(okay - the singing did feature a bit…😉) Changing the direction of your life is a little bit like growing things from seed. Some of those early shoots (ideas) don’t develop at all, some bolt too fast and become too big, too messy and overgrown, and some flourish and grow at just the right pace until you’re ready to harvest them.  Be patient with yourself and nurture those little ideas, those secret ambitions and those dreams to do something different. Start with the small things and the small changes and let them put down firm roots (..and don’t forget that even the strongest plants have benefitted from a bit of manure thrown their way at some point!) I stared at this part of my garden for nine years before I put my dreams for a kitchen garden properly into action, but like most things that bring happiness, it was worth the wait. Remember - Patience, self belief and self care always…and the little shoots will follow. Happy Monday. 🌱💚🌸xx

AD | When @katespadeny asked whether I’d like to style a table using their Daisy range collection it felt like a serendipitous match made in heaven. After all, I named one of my daughters ‘Daisy’ and these little ray of sunshine flowers are therefore close to my heart.
I tend to be a rather spontaneous and instinctive hostess however, I am guided by a few simple rules, which makes the actual planning of an event at short notice relatively straightforward and fun. I truly believe that when you start with a theme, any occasion can by styled and thoughtfully decorated, no matter how big or small. I’ll happily style anything from tea for two to a larger scale party or fete, and no sandwich is knowingly left languishing sadly on a paper plate on my watch – even the most modest of meals deserves a good send off – and the Kate Spade NewYork serve ware was an elegant and joyful choice! Head over to @katespadeny and click the link for their YouTube channel to see this particular tea party come together and you’ll hear some of my top entertaining tips too.
#loveinspades

node.text:
(Ad/pr stay) I must confess that one of the things that first compelled me to use Instagram was when the trend moved from featuring what everyone had for breakfast to seeing people sharing their home style, garden and interior design ideas. I’m incredibly nosey at heart and I like nothing better than seeing the way other peoples lifestyle choices dictate how they decorate. Contrary to popular belief, I don’t dislike modern interiors - I like looking at ALL interiors - I just prefer my own to have a few charmingly broken springs and feature far too many frilly cushions. However, whatever the interior style, my favourite homes all speak of individuality, personality and self belief in ones choices. If I see a modern box, then I like to see passion and conviction in that minimalism, and if it’s maximalism - then I love each unnecessary object to tell a story or mean something that ensures that it becomes a ‘necessity’ to its owner. In fact, in another life I’m sure that I would have been an estate agent or at least a house finder if it meant that I could spend time looking inside random beautiful homes! During my recent jaunt to London, I was asked whether I wanted to try staying at a property listed on a newly started short stay booking platform called @smarterstays It was recommended to me by some IG friends and started by a lovely chap called Guy van der Westhuizen. I mention this not because I have to, but because Guy was very nice, our one night stay was a truly lovely experience and I simply wanted to recommend it to anyone looking for a lovely place to stay whilst visiting London (and who would rather stay in a home environment rather than a hotel.) Oh - and they have also made a commitment to carbon offsetting and have a charitable foundation called #stayforgood 
Of course I also have my selfish reasons for the mention. I couldn’t help but take a few snaps to show you - especially the rainbow library to end all rainbow libraries - and yes - despite the colourful organisation, I’m sure that the owners read all of their books too! (Believe me - I’m asked that same question about my bookshelf a LOT! 😂) Enjoy! xx
#interiors #stylishinteriors
